WEBVTT

1
00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:15.528
Here's a trick prop traders use that sounds like cheating,
but is really just smart math. If one account can't
survive your worst losing streak, run several, and rotate
between them. This lab shows you exactly how.

2
00:00:16.128 --> 00:00:30.576
It's Account Portfolio Cycling, in Step three. Instead of
firing every trade on one account, it spreads your trade
stream across several prop accounts. So when the
inevitable losing streak finally hits, it lands on one
account, not all of them at once.

3
00:00:31.176 --> 00:00:47.376
The mechanic is gap rotation. With five accounts and one
firing per trade, each account sits out four trades
between fires. A four gap. The losing streak gets diluted
across the rotation, so no single account takes the full
hit. The sick account bleeds while the others keep
banking.

4
00:00:47.976 --> 00:01:02.256
Size lets you fire more than one account on each trade.
One times, two times, three times. Each firing account
takes the full trade, so two times doubles your total P
and L, and doubles your risk. It is the growth versus
survival dial.

5
00:01:02.856 --> 00:01:18.672
And down here, it tracks every account individually. Its
net, its peak, and its trailing drawdown. That trailing
drawdown is exactly what a prop firm watches to bust you.
So you can see, before risking a cent, whether any account
in the rotation would breach its limit.

6
00:01:19.272 --> 00:01:32.640
This turns I can't pass with one account into a real
question. How many accounts, at what size, will survive my
worst streak and still flip? It's the math behind running
a prop portfolio, instead of gambling one evaluation at a
time.

7
00:01:33.240 --> 00:01:36.912
One account survives luck. A rotation survives the streak.
